# Windows Performance Tune-Up Lab Guide

This lab is designed for **IT Students (Generalist Track)** to practice Windows system maintenance and optimization. By completing this lab, students will learn how to troubleshoot slow performance, tune up a Windows computer, and apply preventive maintenance techniques.

---

## ğŸ¯ Objectives
- Identify causes of slow system performance.
- Perform tune-up and optimization tasks on a Windows PC.
- Create a routine checklist for daily, weekly, and monthly maintenance.
- Apply hands-on commands and tools to improve performance.

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Prerequisites
- A Windows 10 or Windows 11 computer (physical or virtual machine).
- Local Administrator privileges.
- Internet connection (for updates and downloads).

---

## ğŸ”¹ Part 1: Tune-Up and Optimization Steps

### 1. Check Resource Usage
- Press **Ctrl + Shift + Esc** to open **Task Manager**.
- Click **More details** (if in compact view).
- Sort by **CPU**, **Memory**, or **Disk** usage.
- End non-essential tasks by right-clicking â†’ **End task**.

### 2. Manage Startup Programs
- **Windows 10/11:** Task Manager â†’ **Startup** tab â†’ Disable unnecessary programs.
- **Windows 11 alternate path:** Settings â†’ Apps â†’ Startup â†’ toggle off unneeded apps.

### 3. Remove Bloatware & Unused Apps
- Settings â†’ Apps â†’ Apps & Features (Win10) or Installed Apps (Win11).
- Select unwanted apps â†’ **Uninstall**.

### 4. Optimize Disk Usage
- **Disk Cleanup:** Start â†’ type `Disk Cleanup` â†’ select C: â†’ **Clean up system files**.
- **Storage Sense:** Settings â†’ System â†’ Storage â†’ enable **Storage Sense** â†’ **Run now**.
- **Optimize Drives:** Start â†’ type `Defragment and Optimize Drives` â†’ select C: â†’ **Optimize**.

### 5. Adjust Performance Settings
- Right-click Start â†’ System â†’ Advanced system settings â†’ **Performance Settings**.
- Select **Adjust for best performance** or customize visual effects.
- Adjust Power Plan: Settings â†’ System â†’ Power & battery â†’ Power mode â†’ **Best performance**.

### 6. Keep Windows & Drivers Updated
- Settings â†’ Windows Update â†’ **Check for updates**.
- Device Manager â†’ expand **Display adapters** / **Network adapters** â†’ right-click â†’ **Update driver**.

### 7. Scan for Malware
- Open **Windows Security** â†’ Virus & threat protection â†’ **Full scan**.
- (Optional) Run Malwarebytes for extra scanning.

### 8. Free Up RAM & Storage
- Close unused browser tabs and extensions.
- Move large files to external storage or cloud.
- Clear %temp% folder:
  ```
  Win + R â†’ type %temp% â†’ Ctrl + A â†’ Delete
  ```

### 9. Advanced Tweaks
- Disable background apps:
  - Windows 10: Settings â†’ Privacy â†’ Background apps.
  - Windows 11: Settings â†’ Apps â†’ Installed apps â†’ Advanced options â†’ Background permissions â†’ set to **Never**.
- Check TRIM for SSD:
  ```
  fsutil behavior query DisableDeleteNotify
  ```
  (0 = enabled, 1 = disabled)

### 10. Hardware Considerations
- Upgrade HDD â†’ SSD.
- Add more RAM if usage > 80%.
- Physically clean dust from fans/vents.

